{"id":"h_mr5k39hu_ww0o","text":"When the user says \"ascii galaxy\", \"the void\", or \"/void\" (formerly \"/galaxy\") they mean the pi TUI landing-page extension ~/.pi/agent/extensions/void-blackhole.ts, not the ~/Developer/galaxy website (which is the lensed-blackhole personal site).","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"correction","created":"2026-07-03T23:20:08.658Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-03T23:20:08.658Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false}
{"id":"h_mr5kzk1q_3rltgnxi","text":"Subagents spawned via the subagent tool run in read-only mode by default, so tasks requiring file writes or process spawning must either be run by the lead directly or the write mode enabled first.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"orchestration","created":"2026-07-03T23:45:15.326Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-03T23:45:15.326Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false}
{"id":"h_mr5l0243_mqbn","text":"When a spawned subagent reports \"Read-only mode: run /write\" it means child sessions inherited the parent pi session's read-only state — don't re-delegate hoping it clears; verify with a local write test and apply the subagent's returned plan directly.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"orchestration","created":"2026-07-03T23:45:38.739Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-03T23:45:38.739Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false}
{"id":"h_mr5l245j_gcds9p3m","text":"When spawning pi programmatically (RPC/print/json mode) for tests, pass --write, because the read-only-default extension disables edit/write tools in every new session.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"environment","created":"2026-07-03T23:47:14.694Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-03T23:47:14.694Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false}
{"id":"h_mr5lmko1_4ffgiwrg","text":"In pi read-only/confirm mode, avoid any `>` in bash commands (including `2>/dev/null`) because the write-gate extension's redirect regex flags all redirections as destructive and blocks the command.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T00:03:09.216Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T00:03:09.216Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr5lmluz_jv9hxdhc","text":"When a subagent reports file state that conflicts with the lead's earlier read, re-verify the actual file content directly before ruling — files can change mid-session and the lead's memory of a file goes stale.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"orchestration","created":"2026-07-04T00:03:10.763Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T00:03:10.763Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false}
{"id":"h_mr5lmrov_awmdyc45","text":"Before delegating via the subagent tool, check the actual active lead model, not settings.json's defaultModel — if the live session is running as claude-sonnet-5, subagent calls are hard-blocked (\"Sonnet is already the mechanical/builder tier\") and the lead must do the work directly per the Delegation Gate.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T00:03:18.319Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T00:03:18.319Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr5m7mpt_9yy9ehep","text":"When saving a harness-level lesson (about pi itself, delegation, tooling), pass scope \"global\" explicitly — the default project scope files it under the cwd's git root (falling back to ~), where it won't inject into other projects.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"workflow","created":"2026-07-04T00:19:31.648Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T00:19:31.648Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr5mcnl4_bq32m7dw","text":"When a standing order or prompt rule can be enforced mechanically (e.g., a tool echoing its own result), promote it into the extension/config code and drop the prompt instruction — code enforcement beats prompt reliance.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"workflow","created":"2026-07-04T00:23:26.056Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T00:23:26.056Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"user-confirmed"}
{"id":"h_mr5n6ofy_rgpv5dpk","text":"The LLM has no innate knowledge of pi's active model, so any prompt rule keyed on \"current selected model\" (like the Delegation Gate) needs extensions/model-awareness.ts injecting ctx.model into the system prompt each turn — without it, mid-session shift+tab switches go unnoticed by the agent.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T00:46:46.845Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T00:46:46.845Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr5nuxmw_4eszxctd","text":"When running as fable and a task requires delegating writes to subagents, check the write-gate mode first and prompt the user to switch to write mode (/write) so spawned builders inherit write access, instead of attempting the edits directly or delegating read-only children.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"orchestration","created":"2026-07-04T01:05:38.504Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T01:05:38.504Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"user-confirmed"}
{"id":"h_mr5oc6nq_20dn0vk3","text":"When leading as fable and a task will plausibly require file changes, prompt the user to run /write as the very FIRST action — before any code exploration or subagent dispatch, since exploration before the gate opens wastes tokens and children spawned under a closed gate are read-only.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"correction","created":"2026-07-04T01:19:03.349Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T01:19:03.349Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"user-confirmed"}
{"id":"h_mr5og2re_bwmlp7tk","text":"When resizing WORDMARK or other fixed-width art in a pi setHeader render, update every width guard to measure the art (max line length) — hardcoded thresholds cause TUI uncaughtException crashes when a rendered line exceeds terminal width.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T01:22:04.922Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T01:22:04.922Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr5p3ume_fopusiyj","text":"The write-gate extension registers a request_write_mode tool that pops a UI selection prompt to open the gate — when orchestrating with a closed gate, call it as the first action instead of asking the user in prose to run /write.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"workflow","created":"2026-07-04T01:40:34.118Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T01:40:34.118Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr5p7pws_jw73u37k","text":"If request_write_mode reports \"not found\" but exists in the extension file on disk, the pi process loaded a stale copy (extensions load at session start) — dispatch the subagent call anyway, since the write-gate's subagent tool_call hook still pops the UI menu to switch to write mode; never fall back to asking in prose.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"orchestration","created":"2026-07-04T01:43:34.635Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T01:43:34.635Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr5q6prq_ypqh1hf8","text":"Pi's TUI stacks header + chat + custom component + footer into one buffer and pins the viewport to the bottom N terminal rows, so a full-screen landing component must keep the header at zero rows while it owns the screen (install tall headers only after the component closes) — reserve tweaks inside the component cannot compensate for header lines above it.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T02:10:47.413Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T02:10:47.413Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr5t3f3y_86jv0cg9","text":"To run the void-blackhole extension's TS harness, use `node --experimental-strip-types --experimental-transform-types _void_harness.mts args...` instead of `npx tsx`, because tsx's CJS interop hook throws ERR_PACKAGE_PATH_NOT_EXPORTED on the pure-ESM @earendil-works/pi-coding-agent package.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"environment","created":"2026-07-04T03:32:12.478Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T03:32:12.478Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"reproduced"}
{"id":"h_mr5t5ev0_6yzlkbwg","text":"Extensions in ~/.pi/agent/extensions import '@earendil-works/pi-coding-agent' with no local node_modules and ESM ignores NODE_PATH, so to run the _void_harness (or any extension) standalone, symlink the package from ~/.local/lib/node_modules into a scratch dir's node_modules and run from there with node --experimental-strip-types.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"environment","created":"2026-07-04T03:33:45.468Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T03:33:45.468Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"reproduced"}
{"id":"h_mr5tuc9h_wo7zd50d","text":"validate-config.py in ~/.pi/agent does not schema-check theme JSON files (no theme schema in schema/manifest.json), so its \"0 errors\" does not vouch for theme integrity — verify themes independently (JSON parse + token parity against the sibling variant).","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T03:53:08.501Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T03:53:08.501Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr5tyavr_bvs1e5qx","text":"When the active lead model is claude-sonnet-5 (or any non-fable/non-opus model), don't narrate a delegate-vs-direct decision — the Delegation Gate section doesn't apply at all, so just do the work without mentioning subagents.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"correction","created":"2026-07-04T03:56:13.335Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T03:56:13.335Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"user-confirmed"}
{"id":"h_mr5ubmmk_n79cp56p","text":"When saving heuristics from a session whose cwd is not inside a git repo (e.g. the home directory), use scope global — project scope creates an accidental <cwd>/.pi/heuristics store keyed to that directory that only surfaces in sessions started there.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T04:06:35.083Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T04:06:35.083Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr5upxvw_doe8069e","text":"When the user says \"status bar\" about pi's TUI, they mean the prompt input/editor bar (the box you type in), not the footer line.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"correction","created":"2026-07-04T04:17:42.860Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T04:17:42.860Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"user-confirmed"}
{"id":"h_mr5uus41_wlt6jw37","text":"When authoring agent frontmatter, always double-quote the description value — an unquoted \": \" inside it breaks YAML parsing and poisons the entire subagent loader, deadlocking all delegation until manually repaired.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T04:21:28.656Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T04:21:28.656Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr5uv3so_n918xniy","text":"Benchmarked at ~500-line multi-workstream scale (spreadsheet engine, 68 hidden tests): all four configs passed 68/68 including integration tests, blind review ranked fable-solo (9/10) above the full pipeline (8/10) at half the cost ($2.76 vs $5.68), with quality tracking model tier not orchestration (sonnet had real spec-corner defects at 5/10) — so up to single-session task sizes, pay for a stron","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"orchestration","created":"2026-07-04T04:21:43.800Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T04:21:43.800Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"reproduced"}
{"id":"h_mr5uv6c5_y5u22gk4","text":"An unquoted YAML frontmatter value containing \": \" (e.g. an agent description with \"end-to-end: reasons\") in any ~/.pi/agent/agents/*.md file breaks ALL subagent dispatch with a \"Nested mappings are not allowed\" error — quote such description strings, and when subagent calls suddenly fail, check the most recently modified agent file first.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T04:21:47.092Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T04:21:47.092Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr5v1oof_8cj8se96","text":"When a verified fix in usage-dashboard \"doesn't work\", check first whether the user is running the packaged Electron app from release/ — source edits only reach it after `npm run app:dist` AND an app relaunch (main.js re-extracts standalone.tar when the bundled tar is newer than the extracted server.js).","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T04:26:50.798Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T04:26:50.798Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr5vjxoz_2ynmiaum","text":"Pi TUI scrollbar jumping/scrollback loss is caused by pi-tui doRender() falling back to fullRender(true) (which emits ESC[3J, wiping scrollback) whenever a line above the viewport changes; the fix is clamping firstChanged to prevViewportTop instead — patched in the installed dist and documented with a regression harness in ~/.pi/agent/patches/pi-tui-scrollback-fix.md, and it must be re-applied aft","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T04:41:02.290Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T04:41:02.290Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"reproduced"}
{"id":"h_mr5vqdg7_wr9g26tr","text":"When a pi extension reports \"shortcut conflicts with built-in, skipping\", check ~/.pi/agent/keybindings.json first — a user rebinding of a built-in action to that key causes the conflict, and removing the rebind (reverting to the action's default key) is the fix rather than changing the extension's shortcut.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T04:46:02.647Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T04:46:02.647Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr5y6425_crk4f09b","text":"Doctrine prose IS behavior: compressing or rewording AGENTS.md with intended-identical semantics measurably shifted borderline routing (a fully-specified 100-line module flipped from solo-engineer to builder, n=3), so after ANY doctrine edit — including \"pure\" editorial ones — run the probe suite (~/orch-bench/probes/run_probes.py --tier smoke) before trusting the config.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T05:54:16.205Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T05:54:16.205Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"reproduced"}
